cvrf:Acknowledgment.cvrf:Description: Internally discovered and reported by Gwendal Guégniaud of Fortinet Product Security Team.

cvrf:Note.#text: An improper limitation of a pathname to a restricted directory vulnerability ('path traversal') [CWE-22] in FortiManager, FortiOS, FortiProxy, FortiRecorder, FortiVoice and FortiWeb may allow a remote authenticated attacker with access to the security fabric interface and port to write arbitrary files and a remote unauthenticated attacker with the same network access to delete an arbitrary folder.
